The construction of Okan, a 70-story mixed-use tower at 555 North Miami Ave has begun. This is according to Okan Group which maintains an enormous portfolio of recognized mixed-use projects. These projects have won the business a global name in the construction, banking, textile, manufacturing, and tourist industries. The Okan mixed-use tower includes 163 Sky Residences with special owner-only facilities. A 316-key Hilton Miami Bayfront Hotel with a complete array of amenities and entertainment spaces are also included. Furthermore, there will be 236 Short-Term Rental Residences powered by Hilton Hotels & Resorts. Featured as well is 64,000 square feet of ‘Class A’ office space. Residents will enjoy ground-floor arrival entry with dedicated 24-hour reception and concierge, in addition to a 70th-floor rooftop pool. There will also be a sky deck with private cabanas and magnificent views of downtown and Biscayne Bay. A 12th-floor lap pool with a clubroom and indoor and outdoor lounges are among the amenities. Fortune Development Sales are the only marketer and seller of Okan Tower. Behar Font & Partners designed the tower which features a distinctive curving façade inspired by the Turkish national flower, the tulip. “We are ecstatic to mark this historic milestone and the commencement of work on Okan Tower. It is an honour and a joy to be working on our first large mixed-use project in Miami. Our goal for Okan Tower is to contribute something absolutely unique to the neighbourhood while also introducing a new paradigm for living Downtown. Also Read: US$ 61M+ Loan Secured for UNI Tower Project in Miami, Florida We’re grateful to all of the municipal authorities who have supported the project and share our vision for the future of Downtown Miami,” said Bekir Okan, Chairman of Okan Group and worldwide property mogul and developer of Okan Tower. Once completed in 2026, the Okan Tower will be one of Miami’s tallest structures standing at a height of 902 feet.